name: cppheaderparser
summary: parse c++ header files and generate a data structure representing the class
documentation_summary: CppHeaderParser is a Python package designed to parse C++ header files and generate a data structure representing the class. Authored by Jashua Cloutier and released under the BSD License, it requires the PLY external module. The package, at version 2.7.4 as of November 22, 2016, supports both Python 2 and 3. It is intended for developers and is OS independent. The package allows for parsing of classes, methods, properties, and supports various C++ and Python features. It includes examples of parsing C++ classes and using the parsed data in Python, demonstrating its utility in software development, particularly in code generation, compilers, and disassemblers.
